  urldate = {2025-03-25},
  abstract = {We have obtained spectra of the J=2-1 and J=10-9 transitions of cyanoacetylene (\textbackslash hc3n) toward a collection of positions in the most prominent filament, B213, in the Taurus molecular cloud. The analysis of the excitation conditions of these transitions reveals an average gas H\$\_2\$ volume density of \$(1.8\textbackslash pm 0.7) \textbackslash times10\textasciicircum\textbraceleft 4\textbraceright{} \$ \textbackslash cc. Based on column density derived from 2MASS and this volume density, the line of sight dimension of the high density portion of B213 is found to be \$\textbackslash simeq\$ 0.12 pc, which is comparable to the smaller projected dimension and much smaller than the elongated dimension of B213 (\$\textbackslash sim\$2.4 pc). B213 is thus likely a true cylinder--like filament rather than a sheet seen edge-on. The line width and velocity gradient seen in \textbackslash hc3n are also consistent with Taurus B213 being a self-gravitating filament in the early stage of either fragmentation and/or collape.},
